6:
Get your butts in gear, you guys!
We're not gonna make it!
11:
Wait... wait up! What's the big hurry,
anyway?
15:
I've wanted to try this Yamato
delicacy for so long, and the day's
finally come. You're gonna love this, I
promise!
18:
And not only that, I hear we'll even
get to MAKE some!
23:
You had me at Yamato delicacy!
But... what kind, exactly?
27: You'll find out when we get there!
35:
Oh. You mean mochi? We've had
this before.
39:
Whaaat? You guys already knew
about mochi?
43:
I mean, we've had dumplings and
stuff made out of it before.
46: It's very delicious. And very chewy.
52:
Aw. And here I was thinking I'd get to
really impress you this time.
54:
But hear me out. Mochi... might have
the power to change Palpebra
forever!
64:
Hmph! I see that you're not gonna
take my word for it. But you'll
understand once you put a little
blood, sweat, and tears into it!
68: So... why am I holding this?
73:
We'll need some muscle to take
care of the pounding, so obviously
that's you.
75:
But we'll also need someone else to
flip the mochi real fast.
92:
Sounds like a plan! Okay, you two...
Let's win this thing!
115:
They're going so fast... I'm getting
nervous.
118:
Maybe a cheer of our own will help
them with their timing! Like, um...
124:
Let's go, Stella! Let's go, Nimbus! One
and two and three and four, pound
that rice into the floor!
138:
It took some time, but it looks like the
grains have finally all become one.
Way to pound, you two!
147:
Freshly pounded mochi... it hits
different.
150:
You're right. This is totally different
than any mochi I've had before! It's
incredible!
155:
Indeed. But how is this supposed to
have the power to change Palpebra?
162:
I present to you, the next step in
mochi technology: Kagamimochi.
166:
This is also mochi? It's so hard... How
are you supposed to eat it?
170:
Yeah, it looks like it's long gone stale.
Oh, but maybe if you roasted it over
a fire or let it sit in some water...
175:
Precisely, Alk! You can always
restore this mochi by boiling it or
roasting it!
178:
And not only that, they can be
preserved for long periods of time.
184:
...Making them an ideal food for
adventuring. I see where you're
going with this.
188:
Exactamundo! Beats munching on
dry bread and jerky all the time,
don't you think?
192:
I guess our normal rations HAVE lost
their spice over the years.
196:
And more importantly, mochi is
deeelish! This glutenous wonder will
revolutionize the adventurer snack
game for sure!
200: I don't know about a revolution...
206:
It's all about quality over quantity
these days, right?
215:
Thanks to the power of the
elements, mass production of food
has become more commonplace.
217:
But nothing can recreate the feeling
of a home-cooked meal!
224:
The market's hungry... hungry for a
new portable snack! And merchants
are looking to satisfy this
ever-growing beast!
227:
Think of the marketing capability!
Chewy, gooey, goodness on the go!
It markets itself!
232:
Whoa, yeah... You could totally make
this happen!
237:
What do you mean by "you"? We're
in business together now, Alk!
242:
I'll need someone with culinary
prowess on my team... and I can't
think of anyone more qualified!
245:
So buckle up, because this ride's just
about to get started!
249: Uh, don't I get a say in this?
261: Well, I'll do my best, I guess.
